text: All units, I’ve shared the temple coordinates!
This "Keystone curse" thing? It’s got some serious credibility!
Anyone who uses it ends up dead!
The records say, "No one who used the Keystone to enter the temple ever came back out."
And yet, the President’s sending everyone in anyway!
The President’s going too, I hear.
That’s our boss for ya, huh!
Impressive my foot—it’s reckless! Not that I hate it, though.
We’ll take point and open the temple gates.
Looks like they’re headed for the Northern Continent.
No sweat! My skills are top-tier, baby!
Even if they rip my wings off, I’ll plow through those waves and get us there!
That means it’s gonna shake, right?
You bet it will! Life’s full of rough waters, kid.
Shinra’s mobilizing the Turks and the army.
Better get your affairs in order.
Personally, I don’t think this temple is the Promised Land.
The prophet’s descent, the blessing of the servants...
You could call it a turning point in history.
Let’s just say the temple is the stage for it.
Alright, you bastards, raise the sails!
It’s about the vibe, the vibe!
Here we go—setting sail for the open sea!
Will you disembark on this continent? (You won’t be able to return after landing.)
Pushed her a little hard, so I wanna give this baby some maintenance.
I’ll fix her up quick and catch up with ya.
Gotta patch up those wings sometime soon, too.
Been a while since I last stepped outside. Exhausting.
Man, the Ancients were somethin’ else!
Born of the Planet, speaking with the Planet, opening the Planet.
And then, returning to the Promised Land.
Supreme happiness, the destined land granted by the Planet.
No, that’s not it. It’s not the Promised Land.
Greedy sons of bitches, all of ‘em!
Dammit, what the hell’s goin’ on?!
Don’t say creepy shit like that!
Who the hell are you guys?!
This is one hell of a mess.
Hey, hey, Aerith and the gang are VIPs here, right?
Oh...I guess since I’m only half...
Got carried away with the momentum, but honestly, I ain’t thrilled about goin’ in there.
Thanks for everything so far. You’ve really saved us.
Hey, it ain’t goodbye or nothin’.
You’ll need a ride back, right?
I’ll be waitin’, so make sure you come back in one piece.
Don’t worry about the trip back. I’ve got her all tuned up.
Sorry, but the inside just don’t feel like my turf.
The Ancient has entered the temple.
Then he’s with her too, I presume.
This is bad. We need to hurry.
So the Ancients built this place to hide the Black Materia?
How much is that Black Materia worth anyway?!
The Black Materia’s a secret. Shinra probably doesn’t even know.
Anyway, let’s find it fast. That thing’s ours.
Hey, hey, what’s goin’ on here?
Our common sense might not apply here.
More like the "Land of the End" than the Promised Land, huh?
Chief Tseng, the Ancient and Avalanche have breached the perimeter.
Should we set up an ambush and take ‘em out?
Split into two teams. We’ll confirm whether this is the Promised Land—or something else entirely.
Reno, pair up with Rude. The rest of you, with me.
This damn temple’s crawlin’ with Shinra goons and black-cloaked freaks.
Looks like we’re in for a busy day!
I got a bad feelin’ about this...
Otherwise, this place will just drag us down.
No one’s ever entered the temple and come back alive.
Probably just rumors. Don’t sweat it.
No. Depends on how you look at it.
Was that the waterfall the Shinra guy just went down?
Yeah, looks like it. Wonder how far it goes...
Don’t even think about testin’ it!
We won’t link up with the squad like this! Jump in already!
Let me go at my own pace, damn it!
There they are! Don’t let ‘em go any further!
So it comes to this, huh!?
Hold position here until the Turks give the order! Stay prepped for departure—no slacking!
Feels like the master of a labyrinth, doesn’t it?
What’re you tryin’ to stir up!?
Hey, Aerith...Can’t we tell it how we feel?
No, wait—I’ll give it a try.
I’ve got an image in my head.
The Black Materia’s top priority. No one else gets it.
With Aerith here, we’ll be fine.
Ain’t no way forward like this!
Damn it, where’d they come from!?
Hey, quit yapping and set it up!
You’re just returning to the Planet.
Time to settle a big ol’ score!
First time, right? Then it can’t be helped!
If you fail, just train harder!
We’ll pitch in too—let’s do this!
Yeah, you’re right. Training it is!
Cloud and the others...they’re okay, right?
As long as Cloud keeps it together.
Tifa just needs to yell at him more!
It’s like it’s teaching us how to get along with the Lifestream.
Wait, are we short on Lifestream?
Gotta gather more of the Planet’s power!
We need to stock up more, huh!
Maybe we should take a break.
Big Sis is our only hope~!
Okay, just a little break then.
This place ain’t sittin’ right with me.
But it opened a path, didn’t it?
Whatever it is, we take it down.
Better than no path at all.
Could we drop that and cross over?
This spot’s dangerous. Link up with the vanguard!
Maybe there’s a way. Let’s check it out.
Let’s smash it with this sucker!
But we still need to break that.
Anyway, we just gotta beat this bastard till it’s wobbling, right?
Well, ain’t this a front-row seat!
Time’s short. Let’s take ‘em all out.
Sure, let’s clear the appetizers first.
I’ll show ya what I’ve got!
Gotta punch you once for that!
Yeah, I’m worried about Cloud and the others.
Watch the fruits of my training!
Those jerks did this, huh? I’ll rip ‘em apart!
Alrighty, then let’s head back and do it again!
The seniors are taking their sweet time, huh.
Indeed. But we’re moving out now.
Are you uneasy with just me?
No unease, no complaints—heck, I’m practically a fan!
Pay it no mind. We’re going.
Chief, if we run, they’ll look down on us.
Didn’t you see the flag at the entrance?
The Promised Land is under Shinra’s control now.
Even the Ancients will have to fall in line.
If it’s about numbers, we’ve got the advantage.
Oh, didn’t you know? The Chief and I are the ultimate duo!
In the name of the Turks, I won’t let you through—no way!
They’re just returning to the planet.
One of the Turks went ahead already. We gotta hurry too!
A Turk’s worth lies in staying alive.
Judging by its structure, this ruin is a fortress.
Traces of combat are scattered throughout.
Who were the Ancients’ enemies? Monsters?
Fearing and envying the Ancients’ power, humanity slaughtered them.
They’re just returning to the planet.
No, it’s not. I’m sure it’s not.
You believe me just like that, huh.
This pedestal is the key...It won’t react unless you’re an Ancient.
"O tranquil warriors,  gaze upon yourselves once more."
"The tracks you’ve carved, stained red,  shall become your sustenance."
So we’re supposed to go in there?
Yeah, one by one. It’s a trial for each of us.
Looks like Cloud doesn’t have to go.
If we gotta go, let’s get it over with!
"Don’t forget your anger"? Don’t need to tell me twice!
Testing my anger? They’re underestimating me!
Cloud...he’s been acting strange since we got to the temple.
We’re splitting up from here, huh.
Compared to ninja training, this is a piece of cake~!
Wanna bet some materia on who gets back first?
Hey, hey, this is a valuable sample. Handle it with care, will you?
Alright, good! Hold it down tight.
Red fur, the thirteenth rare specimen.
The reactor, Shinra, all of it...
Senior Yuffie, "act like a cat in someone else’s house", right?
Senior, this time, be cautious. We should avoid unnecessary fights.
Senior, anything left undone? There’s no turning back now.
Since you didn’t come for him, I’ve been playing with him instead.
What the hell’s goin’ on here?
Then that means up ahead is...
Hurry home and wash off that sweat.
Thanks to you, the village’ll thrive.
Livin’ with a reactor sure is somethin’, huh?
What’s wrong? You’ve got a weird look on your face.
Come on, you’re tired, right? Get inside.
Next stop, Sector 4 Slums, Sector 4 Slums.
We’ll leave and breathe the outside air.
If we breathe the outside air, will you get better, Mom? No more shots?
I’m sorry...We’re only halfway through our adventure.
Mom, wait here. I’ll go get a doctor.
We live pretty far out. I don’t know any doctors around here.
I’m going back to my mom.
I’m returning to the planet now.
Don’t be sad. I’ll always be by your side.
We’re going on an adventure together, right?
This child...Aerith, take her somewhere safe.
Hey, there she is, over here!
Death...it’s just one state of life.
Even if the body fades away, it doesn’t mean life disappears.
It melts into the Lifestream, circles the planet, and nurtures new life.
Don’t need to hear that now.
Life doesn’t vanish even in death.
But even if we get that in our heads, saying goodbye still hurts, doesn’t it?
So don’t just say it’s "returning to the planet" like it’s nothing.
No matter how sad the past is, or how unfair things get,
What we’ve done, what’s been done to us...We can’t erase the past anymore.
But we can change what’s ahead.
Sadness and anger make us stronger.
But they can change us too.
I think real strength is something else.
It’s always in our hearts, soft and unbreakable.
If we think about the future, not the past,
We can become stronger than Sephiroth.
We’re out of time. Let’s move.
Your bomb killed a lot of people.
Whatever it is, you can’t comprehend it.
Fill that empty heart with anger.
Let that anger burn away the sadness.
Become the me from that day, Cloud.
You who stand here, transcending the ages
The season of the Cetra, walking with the Planet, is drawing to a close
Soon, the Planet will be yielded to those who pay no respect to history
Having ended the battle with the calamity from the cosmos, what awaited us was further hardship
Whether this too was the calamity’s design
We were robbed, left with boundless anger and indelible sorrow
Now, we face the time of our extinction
Long ago, the northern lands were wounded
All who went to mend it became the calamity
The calamity changed its form—to a fallen mother, a fallen brother
The calamity sowed its seeds—in us, in the children of man
We fought alongside the Planet, and many of our kin returned to the stars
Without merging with the Planet, it merely lay dormant
The seeds of the calamity are sprouting now, seeking to become one
It is our duty to eliminate those who threaten the Planet
The black materia, born of the "Gi’s" prayers
This accursed materia must be hidden from the ambitions of future generations
Meteor will fall upon the Planet, shattering the earth
And after that, the life that remains—
At last, the day will come when Jenova’s child rules the Planet.
And now, the world is no longer one.
A world unbound by fate’s shackles is carving a new path through time.
Along with Jenova, the world itself will undergo a Reunion.
But there’s no need to grieve.
You’ll simply return to the Planet.
Take that! We ain’t returnin’ to the Planet yet!
"To those who wish to destroy the Planet, grant eternal slumber."
If you take the black materia, this place’ll collapse.
Hey, tell me it’s a joke!
If we put the black materia back on the pedestal—
You’re the one who needs to let go!
No good. The collapse can’t be stopped anymore.
Plus, that black materia’s a fake.
Hiya, folks! Been a while, eh?
Leave this to me! You all need to get outta here!
I’m just a fortune-tellin’ robot, after all.
I can’t hold it much longer, so run like your lives depend on it!
Sorry, man. We’re countin’ on ya.
This is bad, bad, bad, BAD!
We said some awful things to Cait Sith, didn’t we?
‘Thank you’, huh? Aw, shucks, that’s embarrassin’!
Cait Sith’s holdin’ on for us!
Yeah, we’ve gotta survive, no matter what!
You’re so loud—just shut up and run!
Well then, everybody...make sure you save the Planet, alright?
Whoa, now that’s a sight to behold!
Can’t let Gold Saucer get lonely without me, right?
I’ve got plenty of spare bodies lyin’ around!
So, did ya get what you came for?
A key to obtain the real one, hidden in the rift between worlds.
We’ve lost control! At this rate, we’re going to crash!
I won’t let you have it.
Come now, you’ll have to take it back.
No matter what happens, we’re in this together.
Cloud, this is the shape of the world.
When the wall of fate shatters, a new world is born.
This Planet holds many layered worlds, and the worlds that are born—
Some persist, while others vanish in an instant.
Even those that endure will eventually fade.
But there’s no need for sorrow.
The worlds that fade simply return to the Planet.
And in doing so, they sustain the Planet’s life.
But if the Planet itself perishes, that cycle ends.
Sephiroth cares only for the Planet and himself. He’d do anything to protect them.
The Planet’s joy, the Planet’s blessing.
It seems we still see the world differently.
It will reunite with our world.
It’s got nothing to do with me.
No choice, then. I’ll lend you a hand.
I’ll bestow a blessing upon you.
Did you bring something foreign here?
But Cloud, just focus on yourself.
Find your true self. Think only of yourself.
I’m the only one who can stop him.
Thank you. I’ve definitely received it.
Thought you’d gone off the deep end with mako poisoning or somethin’.
You can thank us proper later. For now, it’s Aerith we gotta worry about.
Beyond this forest, there’s an ancient city. They say it’s got a Cetra altar.
Sephiroth stole the black materia, right?
If he uses it, this Planet’s toast.
She said a Cetra can stop it.
The fog’s so thick we got separated.
She went off on her own.
You sound damn sure of yourself.
Hey, Cloud, Aerith told me something.
She said Sephiroth totally trashed you at the Temple of the Ancients?
No, that’s not how it went.
Oh, really? Then why’d you hand over the black materia?
No point actin’ cool about it now, right?
Yeah, you’re right. He beat me senseless and took it.
I’m sorry I couldn’t back you up.
You been dreamin’ this whole time?
Eyes were dartin’ around while you slept.
I don’t think it was a dream.
Yeah. I was in another world.
Seems this Planet’s got multiple worlds.
Yeah, and I ain’t in the mood to hear it right now.
Cloud, this fog...it’s not normal, is it?
Doesn’t it look like Feelers sometimes?
So getting lost and separated from Aerith—maybe that’s our fate.
If you feel sick or get weird thoughts, tell us right away, okay?
Like...thinking I’m a fake or something.
I don’t want you to feel bad—just talk to us. Me or anyone else.
I’ve apologized to everyone else, but I figured I hadn’t gotten to you yet.
About that mess at the Gold Saucer—awful sorry, I am!
The Keystone’s dangerous, aye? Thought it’d be better off with Shinra first.
Thanks a bunch! You’re a generous one, Cloud!
No, I just don’t have the energy to dwell on what you did.
Aye, fair enough...But if that’s the case, leave the support to me!
A place where the Ancients once gathered and offered their prayers.
To see it with my own eyes...
Yeah, this has to be it. The city’s called the "Forgotten City."
Gramps told me there’s a Cetra city known by that name.
There’s gotta be an altar here too, right? The vibe’s perfect!
Feelers again? They’re really gettin’ in the way now!
Yeah, the black ones aren’t fate’s enforcers.
The worlds will intertwine and merge.
Anger and sorrow amplify, becoming the planet’s strength.
How’s it look? Pretty good, huh?
We’ve got this in the bag!
Wutai’s pride is on the line!
Don’t get in my way, aye!
Here we go again—the Wall of Fate!
We’ve smashed through stuff like this tons of times!
I’m the last of the Cetra now.
And yet, I don’t even know the words to pray.
That’s why I want to protect them.
Worlds brimming with every emotion will collide.
They swallow petty joys, turning them into anger, sorrow, and hatred.
Though, you might not even notice.
It’s just white as far as I can see.
Still, I’m glad we got to meet.
Worlds converge, then part once more.
Come, Cloud. Shall we have some fun?
Did the Feelers swallow him up?
I don’t get any of this anymore!
And, whatever happens, protect your honor...as SOLDIER!
Hey, hey, hey...This ain’t the end, is it!?
He ditched an important meeting, and I got stuck lookin’ like a fool.
The governor wouldn’t step onto such a shoddy stage.
Got it. Rich kids are a pain in the ass.
Still, it worked out. The anti-Shinra warriors are about to make their move.
Is this war...just a toy to keep me away from Sephiroth?
Guess you’d figure it out eventually.
But the preparations are coming together.
But the preparations are coming together.
Good for you—surpassed your old man.
Good for you—surpassed your old man.
What I want is the real thing.
Ain’t there somethin’ about knowin’ your place?
Still good at stabbin’ folks in the back, huh?
And then they meet once more.
Can’t we push it up a wee bit more?
So, what did Aerith end up doin’?
Don’t look at the sky, okay?
Sayin’ that just makes me wanna look!
You can look, just don’t dwell on it.
Let’s head north. We’re gonna take down Sephiroth.
I get him—I know how he thinks. SOLDIER to SOLDIER.
Everything we hold dear, all of it—it’s a heavy load. Brace yourself.
What’re we loadin’ up? Too heavy, and I’m ditchin’ it!
Don’t worry, I’ll pick it up.
Will the trip back be okay?
What if I said it won’t be?
This is a Cetra place, after all.
I’ll send up a signal flare.
Got it. I won’t miss it.
I’ll pray as hard as I can to stop Meteor.
So, Cloud, you’ve gotta do your best too.
I’ll find Sephiroth fast and take him down.
Let’s win this, no matter what!
If we don’t do it here, the cat’s done for!
Yeah, here we go, here we go, here we go!
Hah! Here we go, here we go, here we go!
Cloud, ain’t you glad you teamed up with me!?
Yeah, I didn’t have time to get bored either!
No need for fortunes now, eh?
Let’s carve our way through together!
Whoa, look at you, all grown up!
Hey, we’re SOLDIER, right!? Where’s that pride at!?
That’s why you did that back then, and why you’re doin’ this now!
If we can just get there...
Rule one of ninja: take out the obstacles first!
We’ve gotta stop it from healing!
Now’s our chance to aim for the wings!
Oh ho, those wings are wide open!
Let’s take out the other one too!
I’m throwin’ everything I’ve got into this!
This thing’s weaker than it looks, huh?
Looks like we’ve got more friends out there.
We’ve gotta break through its barrier first.
We need to strip that barrier off first.
Time for the grand finale, aye!?
This is where we dig in!
Tell me, Cloud, is this reality? What do you think, Cloud?
Aren’t you lonely all by yourself?
Your stance is solid. Your skill...can’t judge it from this alone.
Wandering atop the bridge between time’s gaps.
Hand it over cleanly, will you!?
Well then, I’ll take it by force if I must!
I see thou art a skilled warrior indeed. It seems my judgment was correct after all!
So you’re the one controlling the sand giant?
Lured by the voice of Genji, I wandered into this scorching hell.
How about it? Care for some moonlit sake?
Hmph. I was about to offer a reward, but thou art a dull one indeed.
Hmph! Thou hast stolen every piece of my Genji, yet what else would I call thee but a thief!
The six pieces of Genji thou hast gathered—
Helm, breastplate, gauntlets for both hands, greaves, and then—
The Genji Shield in my possession!
Grr...If I could but gather all seven relics, my lost memories would return!
Whence I came and whither I go, I should be able to recall it all!
Thus, I challenge thee to a final duel, with the Genji at stake!
I am none other than the legendary swordsman Gilgamesh!
The field of battle shall be my island—
I eagerly await the day I cross blades with thee, with my neck stretched long in anticipation!
I’ve got no intention of handing over the Ancient Materia.
Enough! Be silent! I may have faltered last time, but not again!
I’ve waited long, my body burning with desire, as time drags ever onward!
Now I shall reclaim my treasure—
Indeed...Without my Genji returned, my strength wanes...
Urgh...This craving surging from within me!
Have I come here seeking legendary weapons?
Why can I recall naught at all!
Think not that this means victory...
I’ll appear before thee again and again!
Tonight, the Genji shall fall into my hands!
I analyzed the phenomena up to this point, and before Cloud’s location data was lost—
I programmed my data to slip in alongside!
Enough! Vile trickster, I didn’t summon thee here!
Who exactly are you? This space is—
Enough! ‘Tis I who wishes to ask that!
Alas, ‘tis a pity...Is this the end...?
I’m in the privy at present—forgive me!
This is the secret island that suddenly appeared—Gilgamesh Island!
It seems to have been submerged in the sea, yet shows no significant damage.
Likely protected underwater by distortions in the magnetic field.
How did an uninhabited island, guarded by fierce currents since ancient times, come to attract dimensional distortions?
The otherworldly gear we’ve called Ancient Materia—the Genji series—
And the legendary swordsman who’s pursued it all this time—
Everything should now be gathered on this island.
Cloud, I’m counting on you for this final investigation!
Our meeting here is a hundred years in the making! I’ve longed for this day through countless ages!
My Genji, stolen by thieves, I shall now reclaim it!
My once-beautiful, noble Genji—now tattered and worn to rags!
Did none of ye ever maintain it!
Well, we kinda just left it lying around.
Grr...Fools who know not the value of things!
Oh, there, there, poor things. I’ll restore ye straightaway!
The final battle shall wait a while.
Now, I shall perform the Rite of Reforging!
Hah-hah-hah! The true thieves be ye!
Moreover, ye shall atone for the sin of neglecting my Genji’s care!
And of course, the Genji’s ours.
Thou forgettest the duel with me!
Hah-hah-hah! Boastful words from the ignorant!
Very well, out of a warrior’s mercy—
Then traverse the forges, and with the heat of battle, reforge the Genji!
The fiercer ye fight, the stronger and more radiant the Genji shall revive!
Now, warriors all, fight to thy heart’s content!
Please continue reforging the Genji series!
Gilgamesh is waiting in the garden. Let’s hurry!
The adventure surrounding the Ancient Materia nears its climax. I’m counting on you!
With this, the Rite of Reforging is complete!
As a reward, I invite ye all to my garden!
What of the Rite of Reforging?
This place opens not until all Genji are revived!
If thou wouldst enter, complete the Rite of Reforging first!
No need to hold back! Come right on in to the depths!
Wandering, waking alone, a cuckoo calls.
Where am I? A butterfly’s dream?
Forlorn, yearning for Genji, a nightjar cries.
Who am I? A mist at dusk?
Yet now the Genji are gathered, they shall shine!
All of it...I’ve remembered it all!
Who I am, whence I came, and why I wander the dimensions!
Oh, I cannot linger here! I must return to my nemesis at once!
Hey, wait up! You’re just leaving?
In a thousand worlds, only one may bear the title of legendary swordsman!
That fated blade thou bearest—hand it over!
Come, give me the Buster Sword!
A true swordsman chooses not his weapon!
Hmph. I merely spare thee this time!
The title of this world’s legendary swordsman I shall entrust to thee!
No, I still have someone I need to surpass.
Then I cannot yield the Genji!
First, thou must defeat that nemesis of thine!
After that, we’ll have another bout, no holds barred!
I, too, have nemeses awaiting me across many worlds. ‘Tis time I took my leave!
Nonsense! I am the wanderer of time and space!
I’ve crossed countless worlds! Leaping dimensions is child’s play!
Using the interdimensional data I’ve collected, along with pattern analysis of magnetic distortions—
Measuring spacetime curvature and gravitational waves—
Gilgamesh, I’ve located a rift—over there!
Thanks to you, Gilgamesh, I obtained valuable data—
This is farewell, ye mighty warriors!
If fate permits, we may cross paths again somewhere!
For now, this is the end!
Wait for me, Warriors of Light!
He was lively to the very end, wasn’t he?
Thanks to Gilgamesh, we’ve acquired otherworldly data!
It should prove useful in various fields!
First, I’ve created a summoning materia.
The Sword God’s strikes should aid Cloud in a pinch with some lively flair!
Also, I’ve turned the Ancient Materia analysis data into crafting chips.
With these, you should be able to restore the Genji series. Please take a look!
With this, the adventure surrounding the Ancient Materia comes to an end.
But as long as mysteries remain in this world, our journey of discovery continues!
Cloud, I’ll be counting on you going forward!
How about we knock this pillar down?
Let’s topple the pillar and hit ‘em with it!
We might be able to bring this pillar down now.
Next time, I’ll time it perfectly!
Hah! I’ll give it back double!
We’ve got to stop it somehow!
Gotta take these punks out first!
Hang on, I’ll help you out!
I ain’t lettin’ this go on any longer!
It’s my job. I’m getting serious now.
Gotta hand it to the Turks—perfect teamwork!
Can’t we just knock ‘em both out at once?
Can you tell if we should dodge or guard?
Run around if it gets dicey!
Hey, hey, ain’t this bad news?
Planning to move the walls again?
We’ve got to stop it somehow!
Let’s take ‘em out before they get us!
Did the walls slow down a bit?
One more hit and they’re done!
